Name: Trump Organization LLC D/B/A The Trump Organization
Trump Old Post Office
Description: Prior to Donald Trump's official bid for the White House, the Trump Organization secured a 60-year lease with the U.S. government to renovate a historic post office in Washington, D.C., into a luxury, mixed-use development. The arrangement presents ongoing concerns now that Donald Trump is the U.S. government's chief executive. His position as both landlord and tenant opens opportunities for self-dealing that could prioritize his business interests over government efficiency. Additionally, foreign dignitaries and business representatives may book hotel stays and events as a means of currying favor with the president. A contractual clause designed to avoid such conflicts of interest prevents any elected official from sharing or benefiting from the lease. Because Trump did not divest of his business interest upon taking office, he may be violating the contract. However, his interests as either landlord and tenant would not be served by terminating the lease.

Name: Trump International Hotels Management D/B/A Trump Hotel Collection
Mar-A-Lago Club
Description: An Israel-focused charity, The Truth About Israel, moved its recent gala event to Pres. Trumps Mar-a-Lago resort in appreciation of the presidents support for Israel.

Name: U.S Department of Justice
Description: As head of the executive branch, President Trump oversees the Justice Department and the United States' relations with the rest of the world. Through his businesses he still has a lengthy series of financial relationships with private institutions and countries with business before the United States.

Name: Hary Tanoesoedibjo
Description: Billionaire Hary Tanoesoedibjo, Trump's local partner in two Indonesian resort projects, is reportedly considering a run for national office in 2019.

Name: Stephanie Clifford (Aka Stormy Daniels)
Description: Pres. Trump allegedly paid a former porn star to keep quiet about their affair in 2006. She is now suing Trump, claiming the non-disclosure agreement is invalid.

Name: Trump International Hotel And Tower (Panama)
Description: Ethics experts say their fear has been realized as Trump faces one of his most consequential conflicts of interest yet: The Panamanian government has pledged to investigate the Trump Organization for resisting eviction from the Trump International Hotel and Tower. That dispute arose after the hotels majority owner cancelled the Trump Organizations management contract for the hotel.

Name: Metallurgical Corporation of China (M.C.C.)
Description: The Trump Organization’s partner in a lavish Indonesian development project boasting a six-star hotel and golf course with President Trump’s name has brought on a new ally: a Chinese state-owned company. The Indonesian partner, the MNC Group, said it had struck a deal with an arm of Metallurgical Corporation of China, a state-owned construction company, to build a theme park next door to the planned Trump properties.

Name: National Labor Relations Board
Description: As a business owner, Pres. Trump has been involved in labor disputes that potentially could be brought to the National Labor Relations Board for intervention. Since taking office, he has appointed board leaders who have come under scrutiny for perceived business-friendly ties and potential ethics violations.

Name: Trump Entrepreneur Initiative (Formerly Trump University Ca)
Ladder Capital
Description: Ladder Capital, a real estate investment firm that specializes in risky lending, has loaned at least $260 million to Donald Trump's businesses — including $160 million for the ground lease at 40 Wall Street and $100 million for Trump Tower. In February 2017, the firm Related Companies purchased $80 million worth of stock in Ladder Capital.
Internal Notes: 6/5/2018 HN: We should add Related Companies, and possibly the new CEO, to the conflicts list.

Name: Cap Cana

Name: 1290 Avenue Of The Americas, A Tenancy-In-Common
NBC
Description: Real estate tycoon (and now U.S. President) Donald Trump was the show's host for the first fourteen seasons. After he declared his candidacy for the presidency, NBC announced that actor and former California Governor Arnold Schwarzenegger would become the new host of The Celebrity Apprentice. In December 2016, MGM confirmed to Variety that Trump has retained his EP credit on the series. The larger issue for MGM, NBC, and the White House is the payment that Trump will receive for the series. It’s unclear what his per-episode fee is, but it is likely to be in the low five-figures, at minimum.

Notes: Because the company reportedly no longer has an active relationship with Melania Trumps business line and it is not listed as an asset of the First Lady on Pres. Trumps financial disclosure, this potential conflict is marked as "resolved."

Energy Transfer Partners
Description: According to financial disclosures filed in May 2016, President Donald Trump owned between $15,000 and $50,000 in stock in Texas-based Energy Transfer Partners. That's down from between $500,000 and $1 million a year earlier.

Name: Signature Bank
Description: ne of three banks whose ties to Kushner have been widely reported to be under review by New York banking regulators. The bank’s board members have included Ivanka Trump and former Republican U.S. senator Al D’Amato, a dealmaker and power broker in New York business and politics who has been a vocal supporter of President Trump.

Name: Saudi Arabia and Emirati Real Estate and Hotel Deals
Dogan Holding
Description: The twinned Trump Towers bear the president-elect’s name in Istanbul. Dogan Holding, a massive media and real estate conglomerate in Turkey, owns the conjoined buildings and pays the Trump Organization to license the Trump name and brand. It can now rely on that name and brand to be sitting in the Oval Office and singing its praises to President Erdogan.

Name: Jose E. B. Antonio
Description: In October 2016 he had quietly been named a special envoy to the United States by the Philippine president, Rodrigo Duterte. Mr. Antonio was nearly finished building a $150 million tower in Manila’s financial district — a 57-story symbol of affluence and capitalism, which bluntly promotes itself with the slogan “Live Above the Rest.” And now his partner on the project, Donald J. Trump, had just been elected president of the United States.

Name: JP Morgan Chase

Name: Ford Motors
Description: While Trump repeatedly singled out Ford Motors for outsourcing American manufacturing jobs, according to Trump’s May 2016 Federal Election Commission filing, which provides a range of values for each of his stock holdings, he owns shares (worth up to $1 million) in the Detroit auto giant. Google, which Trump accused of suppressing negative Hillary Clinton news, is in his portfolio, as is Berkshire Hathaway, run by one of his fiercest critics, Warren Buffett. Though he tried to start a boycott against Apple AAPL +0.55% in February -- after the iPhone maker refused to help the Federal Bureau of Investigation break into one of the San Bernardino shooters’ phone -- Trump held onto his shares in the tech company, which were worth as much as $2 million in May.

The climate-change skeptic owns shares in Phillips 66 PSX -1.26% - a joint venture partner in the controversial Dakota Access pipeline, where demonstrations are ongoing, and in Kinder Morgan, another pipeline giant facing resistance for its plans to connect the Canadian oil sands to Vancouver, British Columbia.

Description: Trump also has a small investment in Canadian energy company TransCanada, the developer of Keystone XL pipeline, which was rejected by President Barack Obama last year but supported by Trump.

Such investments add to the array of connections Trump already has with foreign entities - including nine figure debts owed to German lender Deutsche Bank and China’s state-controlled Bank of China.

Name: Carl C. Icahn
Description: Mr. Trump has forged relationships with powerful political figures in Indonesia, where such connections are crucial to pushing through big projects. That tangle of relationships includes an Indonesian business partner who aspires to high office; a powerful politician accused of trying to extort billions of dollars from an American mining company; as well as Mr. Trump’s adviser on regulatory issues, Carl C. Icahn, who is a top shareholder in the same mining company.

Name: William J. Clinton Foundation
Description: The Donald J. Trump Foundation gave away $10.9 million from 2001 to 2014, taking a scattershot approach to philanthropy with donations to more than 400 different charities, according to a Forbes analysis of 14 years of IRS documents. Among the notable recipients: the William J. Clinton Foundation, a state branch of the ACLU and a nonprofit run by the New York Times, which Trump routinely criticizes on Twitter. Only $2.8 million of that money came from Trump himself.

Name: Dana-Farber Cancer Institute
Description: An estimated 36% of the foundation’s money went to roughly 100 organizations promoting healthcare, the Forbes examination revealed. The Trump Foundation gave more than $465,000 to both the Dana-Farber Cancer Institute and Operation Smile, which offers free surgeries to children born with cleft palates in developing countries.

Name: Operation Smile
Description: An estimated 36% of the foundation’s money went to roughly 100 organizations promoting healthcare, the Forbes examination revealed. The Trump Foundation gave more than $465,000 to both the Dana-Farber Cancer Institute and Operation Smile, which offers free surgeries to children born with cleft palates in developing countries.

Name: New York Presbyterian Hospital
Description: The foundation gave at least $326,000 to New York Presbyterian Hospital and $250,750 to its sister institution, the Hospital for Special Surgery, which is also based in New York City.

Name: Hospital for Special Surgery
Description: The foundation gave at least $326,000 to New York Presbyterian Hospital and $250,750 to its sister institution, the Hospital for Special Surgery, which is also based in New York City.

Name: United Way
Description: The Trump Foundation gave most of its money to traditional philanthropic causes, including the United Way, a handful of schools, and more than 10 museums.

Name: Related Companies
Description: Related Companies purchased $80 million of stock in Ladder Capital, a Manhattan-based real estate investment trust best known for issuing more than $250 million in loans to the Trump Organization.

Name: Truth About Israel
Description: Organized a ball at Mar-a-Lago to show support for President Trump.

Name: Cadre
Description: A real estate technology startup co-founded and partly owned by White House senior adviser Jared Kushner. Kushner doesn't play an active role in Cadre's operations, company officials say when asked about the president's son-in-law. But he hasn't divested his Cadre stake

Name: SoftBank Vision Fund
Description: SoftBank Vision Fund, a technology investment vehicle that gets almost half of its $100 billion from the Saudi government's Public Investment Fund. The United Arab Emirates has put at least $15 billion into the Vision Fund through its sovereign wealth fund as well. In May 2018, Cadre, a real estate technology startup co-founded and partly owned by White House senior adviser Jared Kushner, is sought an investment of at least $100 million from the Fund.

Name: Marc Kasowitz
Description: Marc Kasowitz, a Trump personal lawyer who has another client with business interests in Vietnam.

Name: Victor Pinchuk
Description: Investigators subpoenaed the Trump Organization this year for an array of records about business with foreign nationals. In response, the company handed over documents about a $150,000 donation that the Ukrainian billionaire, Victor Pinchuk, made in September 2015 to the Donald J. Trump Foundation in exchange for a 20-minute appearance by Mr. Trump that month through a video link to a conference in Kiev.

Name: Quail Ridge
Description: Quail Ridge is a Kushner Cos. apartment complex acquired last year in Plainsboro, N.J.

Name: Penguin Random House
Description: Ivanka Trump was also paid a $289,300 advance by Penguin Random House for her book, “Women Who Work,” which she donated to the Ivanka M. Trump Charitable Fund to distribute grants to support women and girls.

Name: Vegas Seven
Description: Vegas Seven is an online news publication in Las Vegas which Jared Kushner has a stake in.

Name: Veggie Grill
Description: Veggie Grill, a restaurant in Manhattan Beach, Calif. which Jared Kushner has a stake in.

Name: The Patriot Legal Defense Fund Trust, LLC
Description: The Patriot Legal Defense Fund Trust, LLC is a pro-Trump legal fund with anonymous backing. It's intended to help pay legal bills for staffers from the Trump campaign, the transition and the White House. The fund's manager is former Congresswoman Nan Hayworth. Here she is in a promo video.

Name: DAMAC Properties
Description: Trump Organization partner in Trump World Golf Club Dubai project.

Name: China State Construction Engineering Corp.
Description: The Chinese government-owned company was awarded a $19.6 million contract for road and infrastructure work as part of the residential piece of Trump World Golf Club Dubai project called Akoya Oxygen, according to a news release dated Sunday. CSCEC was awarded a $32 million contract to build a six-lane road in early 2017, just as President Donald Trump was inaugurated and it was hired in February to construct one of the buildings at a cost of $163 million.
